## Alice Project — Tech Stack

### Language & Runtime
- Python 3.14 (primary backend language)
- pip (package manager)

### AI / LLM
- Groq API — llama-3.3-70b-versatile (cloud, free tier, priority 1)
- Google Gemini — gemini-2.0-flash (cloud, free tier, priority 2 fallback)
- OpenRouter — meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free (cloud, free tier, priority 3 fallback)
- FallbackRouter — auto-rotates providers on rate limit (120s cooldown per provider)

### Audio
- sounddevice — mic capture + speaker output (Phase 3)
- NumPy — audio buffer processing (Phase 3)
- faster-whisper — local STT, base.en / small multilingual (Phase 3)
- edge-tts — Microsoft neural TTS, EN + JA voices (Phase 4)
- piper-tts — local TTS fallback (Phase 4)
- OpenWakeWord — "hey_alice" wake word, MIT license, no account (Phase 3)
- SpeechBrain ECAPA-TDNN — speaker verification (Phase 5)

### Data / Memory
- SQLite via aiosqlite — conversations, preferences, sessions
- PyYAML — persona config (persona.yaml)
- Pydantic + pydantic-settings — config management, data validation

### HTTP
- httpx — async HTTP client (Groq API, weather, news, web fetch)
- aiohttp — HTTP + WebSocket server for UI bridge (Phase 6)

### PC Control
- subprocess — app launching
- psutil — process management, system info
- ctypes — Win32 API (volume, brightness, window positioning)
- keyboard — global hotkey listener (Phase 7)

### Desktop UI
- aiohttp — serves static UI files + WebSocket server (Phase 6)
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS — dark glassmorphism UI, canvas orb viz
- webbrowser — opens browser tab automatically on startup

### System Integration
- pystray + Pillow — system tray icon (Phase 6)
- Windows Task Scheduler — auto-start on boot (Phase 10)

### External APIs
- OpenWeatherMap — weather data (free tier, Phase 2)
- RSS feeds via httpx — news (world + PH local, Phase 2)

### Development
- Python logging (stdlib) — structured logging
- asyncio + multiprocessing — async event loop + multi-process architecture
